sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J100088
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
[http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_J100071 J100071]+[http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_J10063 J10063]
Green Firefly Luciferase and LRE L. Cruciata (E. coli optimised) under control of cadA promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ben Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Promoter from E. coli geonome, Green Firefly luciferase from L. Cruciata
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Promoter includes Cad1 and Cad2 binding sites. Coding sequence contains Luciferin Regenerating Enzyme and Luciferase coding sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J100071
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The promoter for the cadBA operon in ''E. coli''. It is induced by low pH ([http://ecocyc.org/ECOLI/NEW-IMAGE?type=GENE-IN-MAP&object=EG10131 cadA gene]). CadC senses external pH, by low pH preventing the formation of a disulfide bond, activating CadC. When activated, CadC binds to two sites upstream of the cadBA promoter, Cad1 and Cad2. The binding of CadC to these sites activates transcription by releasing the H-NS molecules that are bound to, and repressing, the cadBA operon ([http://ecocyc.org/ECOLI/NEW-IMAGE?type=ENZYME&object=PD00436 CadC function in cadBA operon]).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ben Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Taken from ''E. coli'' genome through PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We cloned the promoter region 334 bp upstream of the transcription start site, in which Cad1 and Cad2 are included.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J10063
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Green Firefly Luciferase and LRE L. Cruciata (E. coli optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The original part (K325229) was used as the template. We have removed all aspects of the pBad promoter and AraC regulatory DNA. This part now starts with the RBS in part K325229.
K325229 is based on part BBa_K325219. Two site-directed mutagenesis events have been carried out on the luciferase, an Asn286 Ser mutation was used to create part BBa_K325209 which is the green wild-type luciferase. Then a Val239Ile mutation was used to create a green bioluminescence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Malcolm Campbell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Wanted to allow users to use their favorite promoter.
